cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories, as it proposes a framework for optimizing the meta-learning process for few-shot learning problems using neural architecture search. It also involves the use of meta-learning algorithms (cs.AI) and parameter sharing (cs.NE) to accelerate the architecture search process. Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on image datasets (Mini-ImageNet and Omniglot), which suggests it may also be relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
